rComments: Knowledgeable & passionate about what he teaches and at times funny but lectures were very dull & tedious. Slides aren't posted & have no info on them but quotes & pics. Slow on email responses & missing/slow mark returns that you need to chase after. Quercus was never used. Handing assignments were difficult b/c there weren't any links on quercus

When I went into Professor Onley's course, I didn't know what to expect, but by the first class he had exceeded expectation. Professor Onley embodies an ideal professor; compassionate, caring. He gives good feedback and is available during his office hours. You need to do the readings though, if you do you are guaranteed an A+. Come to every class.

Just fantastic. Gives great lectures, doesn't bury students with readings, and his assignments and exams are pretty fair. He's really nice and approachable if you have a problem, and he geuinely wants us to do well. One of the better professors I've had at UTSC. I would highly recommend both this course and his class on the vice regal office.
